er usage, further improving IPC.\n\n**Implementing Early JAL Resolution**\n\nI've successfully implemented an optimization by resolving unconditional jumps (JAL) in the IF stage. This leverages the fact that JALs are always taken and accurately predict their target, eliminating their branch penalty entirely without impacting the critical path. This enhancement boosts CoreMark performance. I've also addressed spurious load-use stalls by refining hazard detection logic to accurately check register usage, further improving IPC.\n\n**Implementing Early JAL Resolution and Fixing Stalls**\n\nI've successfully implemented an optimization by resolving unconditional jumps (JAL) in the IF stage. This leverages the fact that JALs are always taken and accurately predict their target, eliminating their branch penalty entirely without impacting the critical path. This enhancement boosts CoreMark performance. I've also addressed spurious load-use stalls by refining hazard detection logic to accurately check register usage, further improving IPC.\n\ndue to incorrect pipeline bubbles.\n hypothesis: |\n  Resolving JAL instructions early in the IF stage eliminates their 2-cycle penalty, achieving 0 cycles. Concurrently, by accurately decoding the opcode in the hazard unit to check for actual register usage, false load-use stalls are prevented, ensuring the pipeline only stalls when necessary.\n expected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: high\n changes:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"JAL instructions are now detected and their target PC calculated in the IF stage. This allows for immediate redirection of the PC, effectively eliminating the branch penalty for JALs without flushing or causing stalls.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"The EX stage's redirect logic is modified to suppress redirection for JALs, as this is now handled in the IF stage. Trap semantics for misaligned jumps and JALR redirection remain unaffected.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"The full instruction from the IF/ID stage is now routed to the hazard unit, enabling opcode-based analysis of register usage.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"The hazard unit now decodes the instruction opcode to determine if rs1 and rs2 are actually used. Load-use stalls are enforced only when a register is truly needed, preventing spurious stalls.\"\n\n**Implementing Early JAL Resolution**\n\nI've successfully implemented an optimization by resolving unconditional jumps (JAL) in the IF stage. This leverages the fact that JALs are always taken and accurately predict their target, eliminating their branch penalty entirely without impacting the critical path. This enhancement boosts CoreMark performance. I've also addressed spurious load-use stalls by refining hazard detection logic to accurately check register usage, further improving IPC.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"tool_code\": \"write\",\n  \"tool_input\": {\n    \"path\": \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r1s0.yaml\",\n    \"content\": \"id: hyp-20260503-001-r1s0\\ntitle: \\\"Early JAL and precise load-use hazard detection\\\"\\ncategory: micro_opt\\nmotivation: |\\n  The baseline suffers from a 2-cycle penalty for JAL instructions because they are resolved in the EX stage. It also suffers from false load-use stalls when immediate fields happen to overlap with rs1/rs2 bit positions, degrading IPC on common patterns like LOAD followed by ADDI.\\nhypothesis: |\\n  We can resolve JAL in the IF stage, computing its target and redirecting next_pc immediately to save 2 cycles per jump. We can also pass the instruction down to the hazard unit to verify that rs1/rs2 are actually used by the opcode before stalling, eliminating false load-use stalls.\\nexpected_impact:\\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\\n  confidence: high\\nchanges:\\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\\n    description: \\\"Detect JAL and compute jal_target_if to eagerly redirect next_pc when not flushing/stalling.\\\"\\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\\n    description: \\\"Suppress redirect for JAL (leaving it enabled for JALR and branches) since IF now handles it.\\\"\\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\\n    description: \\\"Wire if_id_w.instr into hazard_unit for opcode decoding.\\\"\\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\\n    description: \\\"Decode opcode to verify if rs1 and rs2 are actually read by the instruction before injecting a load-use bubble.\\\"\\n\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n","format":"google-gemini-v1","index":0},{"type":"reasoning.encrypted","data":"","id":"tool_write_jFhGGKcXeGqwxbaEV7oY","format":"google-gemini-v1","index":0}]}},"id":"prt_dedfa3707001P7YzENHyKwdTkZ","sessionID":"ses_212082fe0ffeVvRydscYchyCtZ","messageID":"msg_dedf7d14a0015nGcA0SJxNioF4"}}
