{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777814077252,"sessionID":"ses_212082ea1ffeDbgLtXGU26wj7J","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"tool_write_sf0jQrmQESvUuXeaKm4o","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r1s2.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-003-r1s2\ntitle: \"32-entry BTB with bimodal predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Taken branches incur a 2-cycle penalty because they resolve late in the EX stage.\n  CoreMark's performance is dominated by loop iterations, so predicting taken branches early saves significant execution cycles.\nhypothesis: |\n  Adding a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer (BTB) with a 2-bit bimodal counter in the IF stage.\n  It combinationally steers next_pc to the target when a taken branch is predicted, eliminating the penalty for correct predictions.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 12\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add pred_taken and pred_target fields to if_id_t and id_ex_t structs.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Implement 32-entry BTB. Combinationally predict next_pc. Update BTB entries on signals from EX stage.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Forward pred_taken and pred_target from IF to EX through ID/EX register.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Evaluate mispredictions. If mispredicted, assert redirect to actual correct target. Output BTB update signals.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire BTB update and prediction signals between IF and EX stages.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gemini-3_1-pro-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r1s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/h