low without impacting maximum frequency.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction**\n\nI am implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor operates in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under development.\n\n**Refining Branch Prediction**\n\nI'm enhancing the IF stage with a 32-entry, PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer (BTB) and a 2-bit saturating counter. This aims to predict taken branches combinatorially, enabling immediate PC steering to reduce branch penalties without impacting Fmax. Logic for updating the BTB from the EX stage is currently being implemented.\n\n**Refining Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI'm refining the branch predictor's update mechanism. My current focus is on ensuring accurate propagation of branch resolutions from the EX stage to update the Branch Target Buffer (BTB) entries. This process aims to enhance future prediction accuracy and maintain pipeline flow, all without negatively impacting the maximum clock frequency. I'm utilizing a 32-entry, PC-indexed BTB with 2-bit saturating counters.\n\n**Refining Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI'm currently refining the update mechanism for the Branch Target Buffer (BTB). My focus is on ensuring that branch resolutions from the EX stage accurately update BTB entries, thereby improving future prediction accuracy and maintaining pipeline flow without impacting maximum clock frequency. I am implementing a 32-entry, PC-indexed BTB with 2-bit saturating counters.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction**\n\nI am implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor operates in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under development.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI am implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor will operate in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under development.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI'm currently implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor operates in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted, aiming to reduce branch penalties without compromising Fmax. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under active development.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI'm currently implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer (BTB) with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor is designed to operate within the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC for predicted taken branches to reduce penalties without impacting Fmax. The logic for updating the BTB from the EX stage is also actively under development.\n\n**Refining Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI'm refining the branch predictor's update mechanism. My current focus is on ensuring accurate propagation of branch resolutions from the EX stage to update the Branch Target Buffer (BTB) entries, aiming to enhance future prediction accuracy and maintain pipeline flow without impacting maximum clock frequency. I'm utilizing a 32-entry, PC-indexed BTB with 2-bit saturating counters.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction**\n\nI'm implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor operates in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted, aiming to reduce branch penalties without compromising Fmax. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under development.\n\n**Updating Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nMy current thoughts are focused on refining the mechanism for updating the Branch Target Buffer (BTB) from the EX stage. This involves ensuring that branch resolutions accurately inform future predictions, maintaining pipeline flow, and preserving the maximum clock frequency. I am implementing a 32-entry, PC-indexed BTB with 2-bit saturating counters, and the logic for updating these entries from the EX stage is actively under development.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nI'm implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor operates in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under development.\n\n**Updating Branch Prediction Logic**\n\nMy current focus is on refining the Branch Target Buffer (BTB) update mechanism. I'm ensuring branch resolutions from the EX stage accurately update BTB entries. This aims to improve prediction accuracy and maintain pipeline flow without impacting maximum clock frequency, using a 32-entry PC-indexed BTB with 2-bit saturating counters.\n\n**Implementing Branch Prediction**\n\nI am implementing a 32-entry PC-indexed Branch Target Buffer with a 2-bit saturating counter. This predictor operates in the IF stage, combinatorially determining the next PC if a taken branch is predicted, aiming to reduce branch penalties without compromising Fmax. Logic to update the BTB from the EX stage is also under development.\n\n```systemverilog\n  logic [4:0]  btb_idx;\n  logic [24:0] btb_tag;\n  logic btb_hit;\n  logic btb_pred_taken;\n  logic [31:0] btb_pred_target;\n  logic [31:0] next_pc;\n\n  // PC update logic\n  always_ff @(posedge clock) begin\n    if      (reset)        pc <= RESET_PC;\n    else if (redirect)     pc <= redirect_target;\n    else if (!stall)       pc <= next_pc;\n  end\n\n  assign imem_addr = pc;\n\n  // BTB read logic (combinational)\n  always_comb begin\n    btb_idx         = pc[6:2];\n    btb_tag         = pc[31:7];\n    btb_hit         = btb[btb_idx].valid && (btb[btb_idx].tag == btb_tag);\n    btb_pred_taken  = btb_hit && btb[btb_idx].bimodal[1];\n    btb_pred_target = btb[btb_idx].target;\n  end\n\n  // Next PC calculation\n  always_comb begin\n    next_pc = redirect ? redirect_target :\n              btb_pred_taken ? btb_pred_target :\n                               pc + 32'd4;\n  end\n\n  // BTB update logic (synchronous)\n  always_ff @(posedge clock) begin\n    if (reset) begin\n      for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) begin\n        btb[i].valid <= 1'b0;\n      end\n    end else if (ex_btb_update_en) begin\n      logic [4:0]  up_idx = ex_btb_update_pc[6:2];\n      logic [24:0] up_tag = ex_btb_update_pc[31:7];\n      \n      if (btb[up_idx].valid && btb[up_idx].tag == up_tag) begin\n        // Update existing entry\n        if (ex_btb_update_taken) begin\n          if (btb[up_idx].bimodal != 2'b11) btb[up_idx].bimodal <= btb[up_idx].bimodal + 2'd1;\n        end else begin\n          if (btb[up_idx].bimodal != 2'b00) btb[up_idx].bimodal <= btb[up_idx].bimodal - 2'd1;\n        end\n        if (ex_btb_update_taken) btb[up_idx].target <= ex_btb_update_target;\n      end else begin\n        // Allocate new entry\n        btb[up_idx].valid <= 1'b1;\n        btb[up_idx].tag <= up_tag;\n        btb[up_idx].target <= ex_btb_update_target;\n        btb[up_idx].bimodal <= ex_btb_update_taken ? 2'b10 : 2'b01; // Start weakly taken/not-taken\n      end\n    end\n  end\n\n  // Output bundle logic\n  always_comb begin\n    out.pc         = pc;\n    out.instr      = (flush || redirect) ? 32'h0000_0013 : imem_data;\n    out.valid      = !(flush || redirect);\n    // Predict only if not flushing/redirecting, and if BTB predicted taken\n    out.pred_taken = btb_pred_taken && !(flush || redirect);\n    out.pred_target = btb_pred_target;\n  end\nendmodule\n```\n\nFile 3: `rtl/id_stage.sv`\n```systemverilog\nmodule id_stage (\n  input  logic        clock,\n  input  logic        reset,\n  input  logic        stall, // freeze ID/EX register\n  input  if_id_t      in,    // combinational input from IF stage\n  output id_ex_t     out\n);\n  // Decode logic here...\n  // ... ctrl_decoded is the output of the decoder\n  // ... rs1_val, rs2_val, imm, rd, rs1_addr, rs2_addr are calculated\n\n  // Placeholder for decoded values\n  ctrl_t ctrl_decoded;\n  logic [31:0] rs1_val;\n  logic [31:0] rs2_val;\n  logic [31:0] imm;\n  logic [4:0] rd;\n  logic [4:0] rs1_addr;\n  logic [4:0] rs2_addr;\n  \n  decoder u_decoder (\n    .instr      (in.instr),\n    .ctrl       (ctrl_decoded),\n    .rs1_val    (rs1_val),\n    .rs2_val    (rs2_val),\n    .imm        (imm),\n    .rd         (rd),\n    .rs1_addr   (rs1_addr),\n    .rs2_addr   (rs2_addr)\n  );\n\n  // ID/EX register\n  always_ff @(posedge clock) begin\n    if (reset || !in.valid) begin // If reset or IF provided invalid instruction\n      out.valid <= 1'b0;\n    end else if (!stall) begin // If not stalled, update register\n      out.pc         <= in.pc;\n      out.rs1_val    <= rs1_val;\n      out.rs2_val    <= rs2_val;\n      out.imm        <= imm;\n      out.rd         <= rd;\n      out.rs1_addr   <= rs1_addr;\n      out.rs2_addr   <= rs2_addr;\n      out.ctrl       <= ctrl_decoded;\n      out.instr      <= in.instr;\n      out.valid      <= 1'b1;\n      out.pred_taken <= in.pred_taken;\n      out.pred_target<= in.pred_target;\n    end\n    // If stalled, the register holds its value\n  end\nendmodule\n```\n\nFile 4: `rtl/ex_stage.sv`\n```systemverilog\nmodule ex_stage (\n  input  logic               clock,\n  input  logic               reset,\n  input  logic               stall,         // freeze EX/MEM register (e.g., dmem stall)\n  input  id_ex_t             in,            // input from ID/EX register\n  input  logic [1:0]         fwd_rs1_sel,   // Forwarding select for rs1\n  input  logic [1:0]         fwd_rs2_sel,   // Forwarding select for rs2\n  input  logic [31:0]        fwd_ex_mem,    // Forwarded value from EX/MEM ALU result\n  input  logic [31:0]        fwd_mem_wb,    // Forwarded value from MEM/WB write data\n  output ex_mem_t            out,           // output to EX/MEM register\n  output logic               redirect ,     // signal to flush pipeline and redirect IF\n  output logic [31:0]        redirect_target, // target PC for redirection\n  // BTB update signals\n  output logic               btb_update_en,\n  output logic [31:0]        btb_update_pc,\n  output logic [31:0]        btb_update_target,\n  output logic               btb_update_taken\n);\n  localparam logic [31:0] ZERO = 32'b0;\n\n  logic branch_cond;\n  logic branch_taken;\n  logic [31:0] branch_target;\n  logic [31:0] jalr_sum;\n  logic [31:0] jump_target;\n  \n  logic actual_taken;\n  logic [31:0] actual_target;\n  logic mispredict;\n\n  // ALU operation\n  logic [31:0] rs1_val_fwd;\n  logic [31:0] rs2_val_fwd;\n  logic [31:0] alu_result;\n\n  // Forwarding logic for ALU inputs\n  assign rs1_val_fwd = (fwd_rs1_sel == 2'b00) ? in.rs1_val : // from ID/EX\n                       (fwd_rs1_sel == 2'b01) ? fwd_mem_wb : // from MEM/WB\n                                                fwd_ex_mem ;  // from EX/MEM\n  assign rs2_val_fwd = (fwd_rs2_sel == 2'b00) ? in.rs2_val : // from ID/EX\n                       (fwd_rs2_sel == 2'b01) ? fwd_mem_wb : // from MEM/WB\n                                                fwd_ex_mem ;  // from EX/MEM\n\n  // ALU calculation\n  always_comb begin\n    case (in.ctrl.alu_op)\n      ALU_ADD: alu_result = rs1_val_fwd + rs2_val_fwd;\n      ALU_SUB: alu_result = rs1_val_fwd - rs2_val_fwd;\n      ALU_AND: alu_result = rs1_val_fwd & rs2_val_fwd;\n      ALU_OR:  alu_result = rs1_val_fwd | rs2_val_fwd;\n      ALU_XOR: alu_result = rs1_val_fwd ^ rs2_val_fwd;\n      ALU_SLT: alu_result = $signed(rs1_val_fwd) < $signed(rs2_val_fwd);\n      ALU_SLTU: alu_result = rs1_val_fwd < rs2_val_fwd;\n      default: alu_result = ZERO; // Default or unused\n    endcase\n  end\n\n  // Branch condition calculation\n  always_comb begin\n    case (in.ctrl.branch_op)\n      BRANCH_EQ:  branch_cond = (rs1_val_fwd == rs2_val_fwd);\n      BRANCH_NE:  branch_cond = (rs1_val_fwd != rs2_val_fwd);\n      BRANCH_LT:  branch_cond = $signed(rs1_val_fwd) < $signed(rs2_val_fwd);\n      BRANCH_LTU: branch_cond = rs1_val_fwd < rs2_val_fwd;\n      BRANCH_GT:  branch_cond = $signed(rs1_val_fwd) > $signed(rs2_val_fwd);\n      BRANCH_GTU: branch_cond = rs1_val_fwd > rs2_val_fwd;\n      default:    branch_cond = 1'b0; // Not a branch comparison, default false\n    endcase\n  end\n\n  // Target PC calculation\n  branch_taken = in.ctrl.is_branch && branch_cond;\n  branch_target = in.pc + in.imm; // PC-relative for branches\n  jalr_sum = rs1_val_fwd + in.imm; // RS1 + imm for JALR\n  jump_target = in.ctrl.is_jalr ? {jalr_sum[31:1], 1'b0} : // JALR target (aligned)\n                                 (in.pc + in.imm) ;      // JAL target (PC-relative)\n\n  // Actual branch outcome\n  actual_taken = (branch_taken || in.ctrl.is_jump);\n  actual_target = in.ctrl.is_jump ? jump_target : branch_target;\n\n  // Predictor Misprediction Check\n  // Mispredict if prediction doesn't match actual outcome,\n  // OR if predicted taken but actual target differs.\n  // We also catch cases where a non-branch was predicted taken (actual_taken = 0).\n  mispredict = (in.pred_taken != actual_taken) || \n               (actual_taken && in.pred_taken && (in.pred_target != actual_target));\n\n  // Misaligned trap check\n  logic misalign_branch;\n  logic misalign_jump;\n  logic misalign_fault;\n\n  always_comb begin\n    misalign_branch = in.ctrl.is_branch && branch_taken && (branch_target[1:0] != 2'b00);\n    misalign_jump   = in.ctrl.is_jump && (jump_target[1:0] != 2'b00);\n    misalign_fault  = misalign_branch || misalign_jump;\n  end\n\n  // Redirect logic: redirect if mispredict and no misaligned fault (faults take precedence)\n  assign redirect = mispredict && !misalign_fault;\n  // Redirect target: actual target if taken, or fallthrough PC if not taken\n  assign redirect_target = actual_taken ? actual_target : (in.pc + 32'd4);\n\n  // BTB Update Control\n  // Update BTB if instruction is a branch/jump, it was valid, and no misaligned fault\n  assign btb_update_en = in.valid && (in.ctrl.is_branch || in.ctrl.is_jump) && !misalign_fault;\n  assign btb_update_pc = in.pc;\n  assign btb_update_target = actual_target;\n  assign btb_update_taken = actual_taken;\n\n  // EX/MEM register update\n  always_ff @(posedge clock) begin\n    if (reset || !in.valid) begin // Reset or invalid instruction\n      out.valid <= 1'b0;\n    end else if (!stall) begin // Not stalled, update register\n      out.pc             <= in.pc;\n      out.instr        <= in.instr;\n      out.ctrl           <= in.ctrl;\n      // Update ALU result, take forwarding into account\n      out.alu_result     <= alu_result; \n      // For branches/jumps, the PC for the next stage is the redirect target if redirected,\n      // otherwise it's the calculated next PC (which might be used by RVFI or future logic)\n      // Note: `redirect` is already handled by the IF stage PC update.\n      // We store the *architectural* next PC here, which is `actual_target` or `in.pc + 4`\n      out.pc_next        <= misalign_fault     ? (in.pc + 32'd4) // Trap at misaligned instruction\n                            : in.ctrl.is_jump   ? actual_target\n                            : branch_taken       ? actual_target\n                                                : (in.pc + 32'd4);\n      out.write_enable   <= in.ctrl.reg_write && !misalign_fault; // Don't write if fault\n      out.rd             <= in.rd;\n      out.valid          <= 1'b1;\n    end\n    // If stalled, register holds its value\n  end\nendmodule\n```\n\nFile 5: `rtl/core.sv`\n```systemverilog\nmodule core (\n  input  logic        clock,\n  input  logic        reset,\n\n  // Instruction Memory Interface\n  output logic [31:0] io_imemAddr,\n  input  logic [31:0] io_imemData,\n\n  // Data Memory Interface (Placeholder)\n  output logic        io_dmemReq,\n  output logic [31:0] io_dmemAddr,\n  output logic [31:0] io_dmemWdata,\n  output logic        io_dmemWstrb,\n  input  logic        io_dmemRvalid,\n  input  logic [31:0] io_dmemRdata,\n\n  // Control signals (e.g., for external reset)\n  input  logic        io_irq,\n\n  // RVFI Interface (for simulation/verification)\n  output logic        rvfi_valid,\n  output logic [63:0] rvfi_pc_rdata,\n  output logic [63:0] rvfi_id_rdata,\n  output logic [63:0] rvfi_result_rdata,\n  output logic [31:0] rvfi_commit_pc,\n  output logic [31:0] rvfi_commit_instr,\n  output logic        rvfi_commit_valid\n);\n\n  // Pipeline Stage Signals\n  logic        stall_if;\n  logic        flush_if;\n  logic        redirect;\n  logic [31:0] redirect_target;\n\n  logic        stall_id;\n  logic        flush_id;\n\n  logic        stall_ex_mem;\n\n  logic        stall_mem_wb;\n\n  // Hazard Unit Outputs\n  logic        load_use_hazard;\n  logic        imem_stall; // Not used in this design as imem is zero-wait\n  logic        dmem_stall;\n  logic        write_enable_ex; // From EX stage\n\n  // Wire for BTB updates\n  logic        btb_update_en;\n  logic [31:0] btb_update_pc;\n  logic [31:0] btb_update_target;\n  logic        btb_update_taken;\n\n  // Intermediate stage signals (combinational bundles and registered signals)\n  if_id_t if_id_w; // Combinational bundle from IF to ID\n  id_ex_t id_ex_w; // Registered signal from ID to EX\n  ex_mem_t ex_mem_w; // Registered signal from EX to MEM\n  mem_wb_t mem_wb_w; // Registered signal from MEM to WB\n\n  // Hazard Unit instantiati on\n  hazard_unit u_hazard (\n    .clock             (clock),\n    .reset             (reset),\n    .if_id_instr       (if_id_w.instr),\n    .if_id_rs1_addr    (if_id_w.instr[19:15]), // Assuming instr is available combinatorially\n    .if_id_rs2_addr    (if_id_w.instr[24:20]),\n    .id_ex_valid       (id_ex_w.valid),\n    .id_ex_ctrl_mem_read (id_ex_w.ctrl.mem_read),\n    .id